<p>Publishing matters to me because it’s the thing that finally lets my work <br>
move beyond the private space where it starts. Reading Hall’s history of <br>
typesetting, desktop publishing, and today’s digital workflows helped me <br>
see how much the field has opened. What once required entire teams, <br>
expensive equipment, and long production chains can now happen on a  <br> 
laptop or even a phone. That shift is what makes publishing feel possible <br>
for me at this stage of my life.</p>

<img style="display: block;-webkit-user-select: none;margin: auto;background-color: hsl(0, 0%, 90%);transition: background-color 300ms;" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/90/Apple-iphone-smartphone-desk-3_%2824031206970%29.jpg" width="800" height="600" <p></p>
